3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the impact of topology configurations on the performance of gossip protocols, which is a topic related to social and information networks. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents an analytical framework for studying the behavior of gossip protocols, which is a topic related to systems and control. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of message loss on the performance of gossip protocols, which is a topic related to information theory.
